name: Lt. Governor David Toland
tweet: Thank you to @cjonline for this piece. Doing authentic outreach and truly listening to the needs of diverse stakeholders has been central to our mission at @KansasCommerce, but there's always more to do. I am 100% committed to doing that work.  https://t.co/VaIx7UYjpU

name: Lt. Governor David Toland
tweet: @m_everyware @GovLauraKelly Thank you so much, Senator Ware. Grateful to continue working with you to move Kansas forward!

name: Lt. Governor David Toland
tweet: Today, I am sincerely honored to accept the position of Lieutenant Governor.   Thank you, @GovLauraKelly, for the opportunity to serve the people and businesses of Kansas. I will continue to work by your side - strengthening and rebuilding our state’s foundation.

name: Lt. Governor David Toland
tweet: I was honored to accept an award recognizing @GovLauraKelly and @KansasCommerce for the return of @MainStreetKS. Thank you to Leavenworth Main Street and @votepittman.  https://t.co/AGXAJlGELh

name: Lt. Governor David Toland
tweet: .@KansasWorkforce's services are still here for all Kansans - but we need to make sure we're doing our part to slow the spread of this virus and keep people safe. If you're looking for employment help, please reach out to our team.

name: Lt. Governor David Toland
tweet: @KeriStrahler @CNN @TimVCarpenter Thanks for this, @KeriStrahler—very cool!

name: Lt. Governor David Toland
tweet: Glad to join @LeadershipKS in #Manhattan this morning for an important panel discussion on higher education. Higher-ed is a critical tool for economic development, and Kansas' network of world-class universities can be a major asset for our state to attract and retain businesses.  https://t.co/FvTBLixIrG

name: Lt. Governor David Toland
tweet: I spoke today with Chambers across our state about @GovLauraKelly's new statewide face covering protocol. Masks, social distancing, limited gatherings and good hygiene are the best tools to keep Kansas open. Mask on, Economy Strong.  https://t.co/gQ9f0CDQ6d

name: Lt. Governor David Toland
tweet: @SecNorman @firstwefeast Not so fast. You will always be the all-time winner of the coolest Secretary title thanks to this...  https://t.co/d2FQmdXx1c

name: Lt. Governor David Toland
tweet: Kansas is full of surprises, and Da Bomb: Beyond Insanity is certainly one of them. Thanks to #SpicinFoods for giving me an experience I'll never forget, and thanks to @firstwefeast and #HotOnes for showcasing this fantastic Kansas product since day one!

name: Lt. Governor David Toland
tweet: Congrats to today's graduating Registered Apprenticeship class! The first meeting I had as Secretary at @KansasCommerce was to greet this class on their (and my) first day. Now, this team is ready to take the skills they've learned and turn them into promising careers in KS.  https://t.co/tzoIyfZT7R

name: Lt. Governor David Toland
tweet: This achievement would have been impossible without the hard work and dedication of our team at @KansasCommerce and @GovLauraKelly. Creative, transparent economic development has gotten us to this moment, and it will take us to new heights in the future. #CantStopWontStop

name: Lt. Governor David Toland
tweet: Congratulations to @pittstate for officially cutting the ribbon on the new Pitsco Idea Shop today! This place will be a powerful asset to help turn ideas into successful businesses in Kansas. And the dragster race was an awesome way to help make things official!  https://t.co/vlfZDNe72x

name: Lt. Governor David Toland
tweet: I could not be more proud of @KansasCommerce. We have the best economic development team in the country thanks to @GovLauraKelly's leadership. Thank you @CJOnline for shining a light on our incredibly hard-working Commerce team. #CantStopWontStop

name: Lt. Governor David Toland
tweet: Finally, the last stop in #Louisburg: the famous @louisburgcider! This place is a Kansas legend, well-known for its incredible cider, cider donuts and fruit butter. If you haven't visited before, you really should (and get a sample)!  https://t.co/AuUBCaYOrQ

name: Lt. Governor David Toland
tweet: Staying on the road, I headed to #Louisburg to tour @BottleClip. These guys make all kinds of essential products for the restaurant industry. Their SPARK reshoring grant will help them bring production of components back from China to #Kansas!  https://t.co/40GqvZ20zX

name: Lt. Governor David Toland
tweet: I made one last stop in #Paola: @DohertySteel. This place does it all - from design to material procurement/fabrication, even on-site assembly. Fantastic Kansas company!  https://t.co/TGuK3kC2Gp

name: Lt. Governor David Toland
tweet: Of course, while I was in town, I made sure to stop by the Paola @KansasWorkforce Center! Our workforce development efforts would be impossible without dedicated teams like this one all across the state, and it's always such a joy to get to visit with them.  https://t.co/OmNklONFaY

name: Lt. Governor David Toland
tweet: While I was in #Paola yesterday, after stopping by the Miami County Commission meeting, I spoke with Miami County Economic Development. There are exciting developments in the region, and it was great to hear an update on what's been going on.  https://t.co/9Ikl9SCZX5

name: Lt. Governor David Toland
tweet: It was great to be back in Iola to join @GovLauraKelly for this announcement. @PeerlessPI has been a terrific part of the #FortScott community for decades, and we are thrilled they're continuing their growth in Kansas!  https://t.co/B690pPP5Bt

name: Lt. Governor David Toland
tweet: "Roll that beautiful bean footage!" Last week, I got the chance to stop in and see the terrific folks at 21st Century Bean in Ruleton with Senator @RickBillinger. This hidden gem in rural Kansas is growing at an incredible rate. One of the most interesting tours in a long time!  https://t.co/3k38mmderg

name: Lt. Governor David Toland
tweet: Congratulations and thank you to @EmpiricalFoods for this new quarter-billion-dollar investment in #GardenCity. This new facility will be a major economic driver for the region. Great news for Kansas beef, Western Kansas and our state as a whole.  https://t.co/gZvE07Xgw4

name: Lt. Governor David Toland
tweet: It was great to join @GovLauraKelly in #DodgeCity to celebrate @NorAmCold's new 148,000-sq-ft storage facility. Nor-Am freezing, storing and processing right here in the heart of beef country will be a major boost to our nation's food-supply chain.  https://t.co/fTDLS6RFYx

name: Lt. Governor David Toland
tweet: Kansas is on a roll, and it's because we’re continuing to showcase our far-reaching strengths. @GovLauraKelly is landing more key investments, fueling our economy and getting more Kansans back to work. Thanks to everyone who made this incredible deal possible.

name: Lt. Governor David Toland
tweet: This announcement is even MORE proof that the state of Kansas is building toward a brighter economic future than anyone would have thought possible. @Amazon is making major investments in two very different regions in our state at the same time.

name: Lt. Governor David Toland
tweet: Having shovel ready sites eliminates uncertainty for businesses and gives KS communities an edge in the race for jobs and capital investment. I've appointed @JClaytonSWKS to lead this important initiative started years ago by our partners at #KEDA. Get your site certified today!

name: Lt. Governor David Toland
tweet: It was great to join @LeagueKSMunis virtually for their annual conference this afternoon. We discussed what's been going on with our state's economy, what we're doing to recover and where we're headed. Local government partnerships are vital to our Department's goals.  https://t.co/DvcIyLS9Hp

name: Lt. Governor David Toland
tweet: Congratulations to @BTBC_KU on this historic achievement. This is a big step toward harnessing the research capacity and talent in our state's universities, and I'm proud that @KansasCommerce was able to help make this dream a reality.

name: Lt. Governor David Toland
tweet: Honored to join @GovLauraKelly to announce the recipients of the Securing Local Food Systems Grants through the SPARK Taskforce. These grants will significantly aid in our state’s economic recovery, while also building a more resilient food system for the future. @KansasDeptofAg

name: Lt. Governor David Toland
tweet: .@GovLauraKelly's leadership made this possible, along with our partnership with @LtGovRogers and @KDOTHQ. The new Office of Broadband Development housed at @KansasCommerce will work diligently to ensure all KS communities are connected. We're walking the walk on broadband.

name: Lt. Governor David Toland
tweet: Thank you, @GovLauraKelly. You said "make it happen," and that's what we're doing. Having a Governor who is committed to rolling up her sleeves to get business deals done makes all the difference for our state.

name: Lt. Governor David Toland
tweet: Got the chance to visit Aerospace Systems & Components in #Wichita today. These guys manufacture pneumatic valves for the #aerospace industry, and have been for more than 50 years in Kansas. This business is one of the reasons why Kansas #aviation is the best in the world.  https://t.co/dis6e22SKg

name: Lt. Governor David Toland
tweet: Glad to join my Missouri counterpart @DixonRob to give an update to the @kcchamber on what's been going on with @KansasCommerce, how #COVID19 has affected the region, our plans for the future and how Kansas and Missouri can collaborate to grow the #KC region. Great discussion!  https://t.co/MUw3PRDpJm

name: Lt. Governor David Toland
tweet: So glad I could join @ModMFG for the announcement of their new facility in the @CityofEudora. This will be the company's first manufacturing facility in the U.S., and they couldn't have picked a better state. Thanks to @GovLauraKelly for her support.  https://t.co/kVPZYdZVAe

name: Lt. Governor David Toland
tweet: Happy birthday to @LtGovRogers! I'm very grateful for his leadership on rural issues through the Office of Rural Prosperity, and I'm glad to have the opportunity to work together for the betterment of our state.

name: Lt. Governor David Toland
tweet: 19 years ago I was working as one of the #capcityfellows in DC. Watched the smoke at the Pentagon and heard the fighter jets in the sky as I tried to get home that day. Remembering all those who lost their lives on 9/11.
